<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-945-650  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 945 650.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Dec 4 1989 n344 p97(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Focus on technical support; Businessland widens ratio of salesstaff to technicians.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Graziose, Michelle.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The ratio of technical-support to sales staff is continuing towiden as resellers hire more technicians.andP;  Businessland Inc has aworldwide sales force of 868 and a technical-support team of1,008, a 1.2-1 ratio of technical personnel to salesrepresentatives.andP;  Businessland intends to maintain that ratio andnot increase its sales staff, although as recently as 1988, thesales staff outnumbered the technical staff.andP;  Businessland'shiring policy is reflective of other dealers'.andP;  One of the reasonsfor this turn of events is the 70 to 80 percent profit marginsavailable on training and value-added services.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Businessland Inc. (management).andO;Ticker:    BLI.andO;Topic:     Computer RetailingEmploymentSupport ServicesPersonnel ManagementValue-Added Resellers.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>